      "avalancheSummary": {
        "days": [
          {
            "date": "2026-03-09T22:30:00Z",
            "content": "<p>You can still trigger a large slab avalanche on some northerly and east-facing slopes where you find a stiff slab resting on weak snow in the lower snowpack. You can also trigger a small avalanche in freshly wind-drifted snow that runs above the shallowly buried frozen crusts. Move away from steep slopes with wet snow later in the day.</p><p>On March 7th, a backcountry skier was caught and killed in an avalanche near Vail Pass. The avalanche released on a northeast-facing slope near treeline, about 2 to 3 feet deep. Our deepest condolences to the deceased skier's family, friends, and community. You can read the preliminary accident report&nbsp;<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\" href=\"https://avalanche.state.co.us/report/741d5676-5242-44f6-937d-fd3ca4983ccc\">here</a>.</p>"
          }
